This function runs the simulation.

execute_simulation.Rd

This function runs the simulation.

Usage

execute_simulation(
  trials_per_level,
  n_nodes,
  clique_fraction,
  alpha,
  seed = 452129
)

Arguments

trials_per_level

A natural number specifying how many times to run each level

n_nodes

A vector of the number of nodes to create a graph with, e.g. c(10) or c(10, 20, 30)

clique_fraction

A vector of the clique fraction

alpha

A vector of alpha values

seed

For setting the seed

Value

A data frame with the simulation results

Examples

library(UWBiost561)
execute_simulation(trials_per_level=1,
                   n_nodes=c(10),
                   clique_fraction=c(0.5),
                   alpha=c(0.6))
